      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To reduce the cyclomatic complexity score, we can eliminate the explicit ternary operator in favor of simple if-else statements and reduce repetition. Here's a refactored version:\n\n```python\ndef process_data(records, mode, threshold, flag):\n    results = []\n    if records:\n        for record in records:\n            status = record.get('status')\n            value = record.get('value', 0)\n            has_active_record = status == 'active'\n\n            if has_active_record:\n                if mode == 'standard':\n                    if value <= threshold:\n                        results.append(value)\n                    else:\n                        multipliers = {True: 1.1, False: 1.0}\n                        results.append(value * multipliers[flag])\n                elif mode == 'advanced':\n                    if value <= threshold:\n                        results.append(value * 1.2)\n                    else:\n                        multipliers = {True: 1.5, False: 1.2}\n                        results.append(value * multipliers[flag])\n                else:\n                    results.append(value * 1.0)\n            else:\n                results.append(None)\n    else:\n        results = []\n    return results\n```\n\nThis refactoring simplifies the logic and also avoids repetition by",
